8 Statement of purpose of bill as introduced: This bill proposes to establish the
9 Division of Planning and Evaluation at the Green Mountain Care Board. The
10 Division would be responsible for preparing a report on the status of
11 Vermont’s health care system that enables the public to understand health care
12 system costs, performance, access, and quality. The Division would also be
13 responsible for preparing a five-year statewide strategic plan for improving
14 population health and for increasing Vermonters’ access to high-quality,
15 affordable health care, including ensuring that Vermonters living in rural
16 communities have appropriate access to primary care and hospital services.
17 The Division would establish total-cost-of-care spending growth targets and
18 recommend steps that the Green Mountain Care Board and others could take to
19 achieve the targets while improving access to and the quality of care. The
20 Division would also develop a proposal for achieving universal access to
